WEBVTT

1
00:01:33.552 --> 00:01:35.596 line:82%
-Gurukul?
-Yeah.

2
00:01:36.222 --> 00:01:39.225 line:82%
My name is Karan. Karan Choudhary.

3
00:01:40.142 --> 00:01:42.561 line:82%
Sameer. Sameer Sharma.

4
00:02:24.144 --> 00:02:25.203 line:82%
Let's go.

5
00:02:30.654 --> 00:02:32.693 line:82%
Hey, gus. Gurukul?

6
00:02:32.774 --> 00:02:33.853 line:82%
-Yeah.
-Cool.

7
00:02:34.488 --> 00:02:36.838 line:82%
-Vicky.
-Sameer.

8
00:02:38.299 --> 00:02:39.488 line:82%
Okay.

9
00:02:40.075 --> 00:02:42.246 line:82%
This was the first meeting
for these three.

10
00:02:42.328 --> 00:02:44.039 line:82%
They did not know then,

11
00:02:44.206 --> 00:02:48.002 line:82%
that this little rendezvous was to pave
the path for a lifelong friendship.

12
00:03:35.633 --> 00:03:37.468 line:82%
GURUKUL

13
00:03:47.436 --> 00:03:48.562 line:82%
Quite a big room.

14
00:03:52.766 --> 00:03:53.797 line:82%
Excuse me.

15
00:03:56.739 --> 00:03:57.988 line:82%
This bed is mine.

16
00:03:59.472 --> 00:04:00.792 line:82%
Is this a bed or a rock?

17
00:04:03.869 --> 00:04:06.080 line:82%
Now that we are in Gurukul,
We have to study.

18
00:04:06.664 --> 00:04:09.029 line:82%
Even if the bed is as hard as rock,
we still have to sleep.

19
00:04:09.583 --> 00:04:11.541 line:82%
Hey, guys. Cool, right? My poem?

20
00:04:13.337 --> 00:04:15.589 line:82%
No one is listening. No reaction.

21
00:04:17.424 --> 00:04:21.220 line:82%
Hey guys, if any of you snore at night,
just let me know,

22
00:04:21.305 --> 00:04:23.221 line:82%
so I can rustle up
some cotton for my ears.

23
00:04:24.014 --> 00:04:26.188 line:82%
The thing is, I really need
my eight hours of sleep,

24
00:04:26.261 --> 00:04:29.353 line:82%
dreaming of pretty girls.
So let me know, thanks.

25
00:04:32.940 --> 00:04:34.024 line:82%
What's that?

26
00:04:35.067 --> 00:04:36.312 line:82%
Who's voice is that?

27
00:04:44.827 --> 00:04:47.235 line:82%
Who is that?

28
00:04:49.540 --> 00:04:54.545 line:82%
That is the principal of Gurukul.
The one and only, Mr. Narayan Shankar.

29
00:05:47.514 --> 00:05:48.891 line:82%
No, thanks.

30
00:05:59.485 --> 00:06:01.653 line:82%
GURUKUL

31
00:06:16.543 --> 00:06:17.711 line:82%
Tradition,

32
00:06:19.880 --> 00:06:20.967 line:82%
honor

33
00:06:22.608 --> 00:06:23.634 line:82%
and discipline.

34
00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:28.680 line:82%
These are the three pillars of Gurukul.

35
00:06:31.892 --> 00:06:35.854 line:82%
These are the values with which
we shape your future.

36
00:06:37.481 --> 00:06:41.860 line:82%
Those who have gone before you
have set very high standards for you.

37
00:06:43.570 --> 00:06:46.496 line:82%
Today, all of them are successful men
in their own respective fields.

38
00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:51.620 line:82%
Some are great writers, great businessmen
and some great politicians.

39
00:06:52.496 --> 00:06:58.115 line:82%
But all of them have one thing in common.
All their lives,

40
00:06:58.210 --> 00:07:01.547 line:82%
they have followed the principles
taught to them by this Gurukul.

41
00:07:03.799 --> 00:07:09.012 line:82%
Today, you have the opportunity
to be a part of this great lineage.

42
00:07:12.384 --> 00:07:15.602 line:82%
You have been summoned
from all over the country

43
00:07:15.686 --> 00:07:20.607 line:82%
because we believe that you
have what it takes to be great men.

44
00:07:22.568 --> 00:07:25.112 line:82%
But success never comes so easily.

45
00:07:25.946 --> 00:07:29.867 line:82%
Behind every great success
lies a great sacrifice.

46
00:07:33.495 --> 00:07:35.664 line:82%
By entering this institution today,

47
00:07:35.747 --> 00:07:37.966 line:82%
you have left behind the world outside.

48
00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:42.045 line:82%
As long as you are here,
Gurukul is your world.

49
00:07:44.047 --> 00:07:47.968 line:82%
We expect that you will study
with complete dedication

50
00:07:48.677 --> 00:07:50.470 line:82%
and follow the rules and regulations

51
00:07:50.554 --> 00:07:52.723 line:82%
of this institution
with strict discipline.

52
00:07:53.432 --> 00:07:56.852 line:82%
If any one is found guilty of misconduct,

53
00:07:56.935 --> 00:07:59.250 line:82%
he will be expelled immediately.

54
00:08:00.814 --> 00:08:06.361 line:82%
And remember,
if you are expelled from here,

55
00:08:07.196 --> 00:08:11.825 line:82%
then the doors to every other institute in
this country will be shut for you as well.

56
00:08:15.162 --> 00:08:19.518 line:82%
So if there is anyone here who
is not willing to make this sacrifice,

57
00:08:21.084 --> 00:08:23.297 line:82%
then he is free to walk
out of that gate right now.

58
00:08:25.672 --> 00:08:29.176 line:82%
But if you have decided to stay here,

59
00:08:29.551 --> 00:08:34.181 line:82%
then that gate and the world outside
does not exist for you anymore.

60
00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:47.194 line:82%
Now I want all of you to close
your eyes, bow your heads,

61
00:08:49.279 --> 00:08:51.609 line:82%
and think of every word I have said to you

62
00:08:52.658 --> 00:08:54.409 line:82%
and to come to your respective decisions.

63
00:10:32.924 --> 00:10:36.345 line:82%
MOHABBATEIN

64
00:12:34.504 --> 00:12:35.547 line:82%
Cool.

65
00:12:36.298 --> 00:12:38.647 line:82%
-Vicky. That's my photograph.
-I can see that, man,

66
00:12:38.730 --> 00:12:41.219 line:82%
-but who's this lady in red with you?
-Nobody, give it back.

67
00:12:41.303 --> 00:12:42.387 line:82%
Sameer has a girlfriend.

68
00:12:42.471 --> 00:12:44.639 line:82%
Stop it, Vicky. What are you doing?

69
00:12:44.723 --> 00:12:46.016 line:82%
-Oh, shit.
-Oh, shit.

70
00:12:50.562 --> 00:12:52.594 line:82%
Oh, God! It's you. You scared us.

71
00:12:52.668 --> 00:12:55.435 line:82%
Come here, quickly.
I've got something to show you.

72
00:12:56.401 --> 00:12:57.595 line:82%
-Okay, tell me.
-Vicky.

73
00:12:58.320 --> 00:12:59.446 line:82%
-Who is this?
-This?

74
00:12:59.529 --> 00:13:02.659 line:82%
Romeo and Juliet. Heer, Ranjha.
Soni, Mahiwal.

75
00:13:03.116 --> 00:13:04.798 line:82%
Sameer and... Sameer and?

76
00:13:05.202 --> 00:13:08.060 line:82%
Sanjana. And it's not
what you're making it out to be.

77
00:13:08.622 --> 00:13:12.784 line:82%
She's just a good friend of mine,
actually, she was a friend.

78
00:13:14.377 --> 00:13:15.504 line:82%
She was a friend?

79
00:13:15.795 --> 00:13:19.633 line:82%
Sanju was my childhood friend.
We were best friends.

80
00:13:19.841 --> 00:13:22.389 line:82%
We were neighbors
and literally grew up together.

81
00:13:25.096 --> 00:13:29.216 line:82%
We had this photograph taken
at a funfair. It was her birthday.

82
00:13:30.143 --> 00:13:33.355 line:82%
And the next day,
she was supposed to leave. Forever.

83
00:13:33.897 --> 00:13:38.693 line:82%
Her father had been transferred
and that was the last time that I saw her.

84
00:13:41.446 --> 00:13:45.507 line:82%
That was six years ago.
I was just 14 years old.

85
00:13:46.660 --> 00:13:48.328 line:82%
But do you know where she is now?

86
00:13:48.411 --> 00:13:51.498 line:82%
I heard a few months ago
that she could be in this very town.

87
00:13:51.748 --> 00:13:54.397 line:82%
That's great! Which means
that you know where she lives?

88
00:13:54.451 --> 00:13:56.807 line:82%
No, I don't. And I don't want to find out.

89
00:13:57.921 --> 00:14:00.261 line:82%
-Why not?
-Because it's been a long time

90
00:14:00.522 --> 00:14:03.085 line:82%
and I don't know if she will recognize me

91
00:14:03.677 --> 00:14:07.286 line:82%
or whether she would like to meet me
or not. So if we are fated to meet,

92
00:14:07.681 --> 00:14:12.477 line:82%
then we will happen across each other's
paths. And if we don't, then so be it.

93
00:14:12.936 --> 00:14:16.314 line:82%
Hey, Sameer. You really love this girl.

94
00:14:16.398 --> 00:14:20.026 line:82%
No, nothing of the sort.
She's just an old friend.

95
00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:21.861 line:82%
Shut up. Just an old friend.

96
00:14:22.075 --> 00:14:25.031 line:82%
Tell me something. How many other
old friends' photos

97
00:14:25.115 --> 00:14:27.247 line:82%
have you been carrying
for the last six years?

98
00:14:27.951 --> 00:14:29.536 line:82%
That's the bell for your love.

99
00:14:29.619 --> 00:14:31.037 line:82%
Come on, it's time to sleep.

100
00:14:31.121 --> 00:14:32.497 line:82%
Old friend, my foot.

101
00:14:32.581 --> 00:14:34.416 line:82%
I wish I had that photograph in my pocket.

102
00:14:34.509 --> 00:14:38.712 line:82%
By now I'd have been in her house,
making her feed me jalebi.

103
00:14:38.795 --> 00:14:42.760 line:82%
And look at you! "We'll meet if we're
destined to, otherwise, we won't."

104
00:14:43.633 --> 00:14:44.940 line:82%
Nonsense, man.

105
00:14:47.470 --> 00:14:50.682 line:82%
Know what, Karan.
There's a girls' college behind ours?

106
00:14:51.165 --> 00:14:53.268 line:82%
-So what should I do?
-No. You don't do anything.

107
00:14:53.351 --> 00:14:56.094 line:82%
You just think. I'll be the one doing it.

108
00:14:57.397 --> 00:15:01.026 line:82%
I'm late. Why do we've to begin so early?

109
00:15:01.443 --> 00:15:03.147 line:82%
Shit, come on, Vicky. Let's go.

110
00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:17.834 line:82%
Who's that? Stop there!

111
00:15:18.043 --> 00:15:20.962 line:82%
Stop it! You thief.

112
00:15:21.504 --> 00:15:23.590 line:82%
Where are you running off to?

113
00:15:23.675 --> 00:15:25.467 line:82%
I'll kill you.

114
00:15:44.402 --> 00:15:49.324 line:82%
Ishika! Miss Monica is coming! Hurry up!

115
00:16:02.545 --> 00:16:06.800 line:82%
Ishika. Love.

116
00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:23.483 line:82%
We're through at last. Can we go now?
I'm terribly hungry.

117
00:16:23.578 --> 00:16:27.529 line:82%
-We've still got to buy mineral water.
-It was available in the shop back there.

118
00:16:27.612 --> 00:16:29.521 line:82%
You guys take the stuff to the jeep.

119
00:16:29.622 --> 00:16:30.990 line:82%
-I'll go and get it.
-Okay.

120
00:16:31.074 --> 00:16:33.957 line:82%
You're always thinking about food.
You know nothing else, do you?

121
00:16:37.664 --> 00:16:39.416 line:82%
-How much is it for?
-One and a half rupees.

122
00:16:39.499 --> 00:16:41.723 line:82%
How is it one and a half?
It's price is two and a half.

123
00:16:41.796 --> 00:16:43.196 line:82%
No, ma'am, it's for one and a half.

124
00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:45.880 line:82%
Look, I know everything.
The price is two and a half rupees

125
00:16:45.964 --> 00:16:49.342 line:82%
and I will pay you accordingly,
not a penny more, not a penny less.

126
00:16:49.426 --> 00:16:52.345 line:82%
-Please try to understand what I say.
-I will listen to nothing.

127
00:16:52.429 --> 00:16:54.414 line:82%
Do you want to give it or not?
Tell me clearly.

128
00:16:54.487 --> 00:16:57.027 line:82%
But ma'am, it costs one and a half rupees,
not two and a half!

129
00:16:57.434 --> 00:17:01.438 line:82%
Only last week my friend bought
the same thing from your shop

130
00:17:01.521 --> 00:17:03.106 line:82%
-for two and a half bucks.
-Maybe...

131
00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:06.443 line:82%
-but the price now is one and a half.
-But I'll pay two and a half rupees.

132
00:17:06.526 --> 00:17:09.015 line:82%
-Quickly, pack it.
-Somebody, please make her see reason.

133
00:17:09.098 --> 00:17:10.864 line:82%
Please hold this. Thank you.

134
00:17:11.489 --> 00:17:15.452 line:82%
We'll meet, if we are destined to.

135
00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:18.621 line:82%
-Are you giving it or not?
-How can I charge

136
00:17:18.705 --> 00:17:20.081 line:82%
two and a half for one and a half?

137
00:17:20.165 --> 00:17:23.491 line:82%
I don't know. I'll pay two and a half.
Here's the money, if you want it.

138
00:17:23.668 --> 00:17:27.050 line:82%
By the way, one and a half rupees
is less than two and a half rupees.

139
00:17:28.798 --> 00:17:30.642 line:82%
Is it really?

140
00:17:30.756 --> 00:17:32.519 line:82%
That's just what I was trying to explain.

141
00:17:33.710 --> 00:17:34.763 line:82%
How much is one and a half?

142
00:17:35.346 --> 00:17:36.378 line:82%
One and a half rupees.

143
00:17:37.724 --> 00:17:40.810 line:82%
Okay, so give it to me
for one and a half rupees.

144
00:17:40.897 --> 00:17:42.057 line:82%
As you wish.

145
00:17:44.647 --> 00:17:46.399 line:82%
-Your bangles and change.
-Thank you.

146
00:17:48.067 --> 00:17:49.077 line:82%
Thanks.

147
00:17:53.448 --> 00:17:54.866 line:82%
Show me these bangles, please.

148
00:17:54.949 --> 00:17:56.037 line:82%
-For you?
-Yes.

149
00:17:56.367 --> 00:17:58.244 line:82%
-What?
-No, for a friend of mine.

150
00:17:58.309 --> 00:17:59.370 line:82%
Which one's?

151
00:17:59.454 --> 00:18:02.457 line:82%
-That red one, yes, the green one.
-That one?

152
00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:06.169 line:82%
Sameer. Sameer Sharma!

153
00:18:09.011 --> 00:18:10.012 line:82%
Sanju.

154
00:18:10.947 --> 00:18:13.738 line:82%
It's you! I don't believe this, Sameer.

155
00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:17.388 line:82%
-What are you doing here?
-Me? I am a student at Gurukul.

156
00:18:17.472 --> 00:18:19.682 line:82%
-Not bad, Mr. Sharma.
-Cool, huh?

157
00:18:19.933 --> 00:18:23.520 line:82%
Which means you've been here for so long,

158
00:18:23.603 --> 00:18:27.315 line:82%
-and did not even bother to call me.
-I didn't have your...

159
00:18:27.398 --> 00:18:29.092 line:82%
Stop making excuses!

160
00:18:29.526 --> 00:18:31.945 line:82%
The truth is that
you didn't even think of me,

161
00:18:32.028 --> 00:18:35.532 line:82%
so it did not bother you
whether I was in this town or not,

162
00:18:35.615 --> 00:18:37.905 line:82%
what is my phone number. Right? Stupid!

163
00:18:37.979 --> 00:18:40.094 line:82%
-Excuse me, ma'am.
-Hey, that's mine. Thank you.

164
00:18:40.338 --> 00:18:41.690 line:82%
-What is it?
- Nothing,

165
00:18:41.764 --> 00:18:43.623 line:82%
just the list of things I had to buy.

166
00:18:43.706 --> 00:18:49.441 line:82%
-Have you found everything?
-Yes. I've found everything.

167
00:18:50.004 --> 00:18:52.512 line:82%
So come with me.
I'm going to set you straight.

168
00:18:52.614 --> 00:18:55.106 line:82%
Who do you think you are?
Being a Gurukul student,

169
00:18:55.210 --> 00:18:57.978 line:82%
it has gotten to your head.
We're going home straight away.

170
00:18:58.599 --> 00:19:01.463 line:82%
-Papa will be so happy to see you.
-Sanju, I cannot come now...

171
00:19:01.554 --> 00:19:04.117 line:82%
-I've to return to Gurukul.
-Promise you'll come on Sunday.

172
00:19:04.198 --> 00:19:06.456 line:82%
I promise.

173
00:19:18.471 --> 00:19:22.848 line:82%
Khan Baba, when does the train
from Aligarh usually arrive?

174
00:19:24.038 --> 00:19:29.144 line:82%
The train should be here any moment.
Whom have you come to receive?

175
00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:31.838 line:82%
-The professor of my college.
-I see...

176
00:19:31.921 --> 00:19:33.465 line:82%
The train should be here any moment.

177
00:19:48.102 --> 00:19:51.396 line:82%
Khan Baba, who's that girl?

178
00:19:54.402 --> 00:19:57.488 line:82%
That's Kiran. She comes here quite often.

179
00:20:00.742 --> 00:20:01.761 line:82%
Kiran.

180
00:20:33.983 --> 00:20:36.819 line:82%
-Hey. Gurukul. Are you from Gurukul?
-Yes, sir.

181
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:39.072 line:82%
-Sir, your luggage?
-No, it's okay.

182
00:20:40.073 --> 00:20:41.324 line:82%
Take this.

183
00:20:50.792 --> 00:20:52.877 line:82%
-Shall we leave?
-Yes, sir.

184
00:21:08.643 --> 00:21:13.071 line:82%
Okay, guys, this is it. I have decided.
First thing tomorrow morning,

185
00:21:13.606 --> 00:21:15.922 line:82%
I'm going to cross that gate,
enter that girls' hostel

186
00:21:16.734 --> 00:21:18.773 line:82%
and wherever that girl is,
I am going to find her

187
00:21:19.362 --> 00:21:24.125 line:82%
and look deep into her eyes
and tell her, "You're beautiful."

188
00:21:25.451 --> 00:21:26.764 line:82%
I am going to do it, guys!

189
00:21:26.995 --> 00:21:28.860 line:82%
Now you guys tell me
what you have decided.

190
00:21:29.622 --> 00:21:31.582 line:82%
What say, Sameer?

191
00:21:33.459 --> 00:21:35.867 line:82%
Is she going to be
just a friend all your life?

192
00:21:36.656 --> 00:21:37.706 line:82%
No...

193
00:21:39.357 --> 00:21:41.426 line:82%
for too many years,
I've just been a friend of her

194
00:21:43.261 --> 00:21:46.305 line:82%
-But now it's time to take it further.
-That's the spirit, my boy.

195
00:21:46.389 --> 00:21:48.224 line:82%
Hey, Karan. What have you thought?

196
00:21:49.058 --> 00:21:51.394 line:82%
I am going to think of her
as a beautiful dream

197
00:21:51.477 --> 00:21:55.023 line:82%
-and forget about her.
-What? Don't be such a sissy.

198
00:21:56.107 --> 00:21:59.819 line:82%
You guys must've forgotten,
but I still remember every word

199
00:21:59.902 --> 00:22:03.364 line:82%
Narayan Shankar uttered.
If you break the rules of Gurukul,

200
00:22:03.948 --> 00:22:04.949 line:82%
you will be expelled.

201
00:22:05.033 --> 00:22:07.555 line:82%
Come on, Karan. Don't be so scared.

202
00:22:07.994 --> 00:22:10.204 line:82%
People usually go overboard
during a speech,

203
00:22:10.288 --> 00:22:12.582 line:82%
that doesn't mean it is set in stone.

204
00:22:12.665 --> 00:22:15.418 line:82%
Every word Narayan Shankar says
is set in stone.

205
00:22:15.835 --> 00:22:19.172 line:82%
He has done it earlier,
and he can do it again.

206
00:22:19.547 --> 00:22:20.673 line:82%
What has he done earlier?

207
00:22:22.442 --> 00:22:23.687 line:82%
It's a famous story.

208
00:22:24.677 --> 00:22:26.738 line:82%
There used to be this student here
a few years ago.

209
00:22:27.638 --> 00:22:31.945 line:82%
He was brilliant. Everyone thought
he would do something in life.

210
00:22:33.561 --> 00:22:34.986 line:82%
But he made one mistake.

211
00:22:36.564 --> 00:22:40.610 line:82%
He broke a rule of Gurukul,
he fell in love.

212
00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:45.710 line:82%
Narayan Shankar expelled him without
