00:47:31.307 --> 00:47:34.143 line:82%
Eat sugar and die! Stupid.

434
00:47:34.310 --> 00:47:36.123 line:82%
Next time I'll kill you.

435
00:47:36.226 --> 00:47:39.190 line:82%
Oh, this is love

436
00:47:40.320 --> 00:47:44.144 line:82%
Ishika, Ishika!
Miss Monica is calling you!

437
00:47:53.371 --> 00:47:54.409 line:82%
Oh, my.

438
00:47:58.960 --> 00:47:59.971 line:82%
Come in.

439
00:48:01.004 --> 00:48:02.338 line:82%
Did you call me, Ma'am?

440
00:48:02.422 --> 00:48:07.135 line:82%
Yes, Ishika come in.
Your cousin, Viren, has come to see you.

441
00:48:08.087 --> 00:48:13.061 line:82%
I told him that I do not like visitors
who do not take prior permission,

442
00:48:13.850 --> 00:48:16.115 line:82%
but I believe
there is some sort of emergency,

443
00:48:16.477 --> 00:48:18.061 line:82%
so I have given him permission.

444
00:48:18.771 --> 00:48:20.936 line:82%
But make sure it doesn't happen again.

445
00:48:21.441 --> 00:48:22.567 line:82%
Yes, ma'am.

446
00:48:28.531 --> 00:48:30.867 line:82%
Excuse me... You!

447
00:48:30.950 --> 00:48:35.038 line:82%
My dear Ishika, how have you been?
Quickly put your arm around me,

448
00:48:35.496 --> 00:48:38.875 line:82%
otherwise I will tell Miss Monica
about your morning visits to Gurukul.

449
00:48:44.505 --> 00:48:46.883 line:82%
I am seeing you after so many years

450
00:48:46.966 --> 00:48:49.052 line:82%
and just look at how you've really grown.

451
00:48:49.135 --> 00:48:51.861 line:82%
Come, let's sit down. Come!

452
00:48:54.140 --> 00:48:55.266 line:82%
Miss Monica...

453
00:48:55.683 --> 00:48:58.102 line:82%
Keep smiling, keep smiling, that's lovely.

454
00:48:58.519 --> 00:49:01.731 line:82%
Now you must be wondering what
the hell I am doing here, right?

455
00:49:02.231 --> 00:49:04.317 line:82%
The thing is, Ishika,
ever since I've seen you,

456
00:49:04.400 --> 00:49:06.319 line:82%
Your face keeps flashing before my eyes

457
00:49:06.402 --> 00:49:09.280 line:82%
and you've even started appearing
in my dreams at night.

458
00:49:09.405 --> 00:49:14.035 line:82%
And I am sure I must be in your dreams
too, right? I knew it...

459
00:49:14.327 --> 00:49:16.663 line:82%
I feel like there is no point
in wasting any time now.

460
00:49:16.954 --> 00:49:19.032 line:82%
If I keep seeing you
and you keep seeing me,

461
00:49:19.125 --> 00:49:23.086 line:82%
but we never say anything to each other,
wouldn't that be so stupid?

462
00:49:23.169 --> 00:49:25.812 line:82%
I feel we should
take our love story further.

463
00:49:26.583 --> 00:49:30.423 line:82%
So I will wait for you on Sunday
at the Mall Road Coffee House at 4:00.

464
00:49:31.052 --> 00:49:35.473 line:82%
-Just be there. Okay?
-Never.

465
00:49:35.556 --> 00:49:38.685 line:82%
-Never? Miss Monica...
-Okay.

466
00:49:38.768 --> 00:49:41.145 line:82%
So sweet. Come.
Let's say bye to Miss Monica.

467
00:49:52.865 --> 00:49:55.271 line:82%
Excuse me. My name is Karan, and yours?

468
00:49:57.078 --> 00:49:58.805 line:82%
Hi! I'm Karan.

469
00:50:00.746 --> 00:50:02.792 line:82%
What did you say your name was?

470
00:50:03.710 --> 00:50:06.568 line:82%
How do you end up hurting yourself
in the same place, all the time?

471
00:50:07.839 --> 00:50:08.881 line:82%
Sorry, what?

472
00:50:09.590 --> 00:50:12.896 line:82%
I asked how you end up hurting yourself
in the same place all the time?

473
00:50:13.553 --> 00:50:18.474 line:82%
I do not know, maybe
my mind is elsewhere these days.

474
00:50:19.767 --> 00:50:21.680 line:82%
Did you always want to be a doctor?

475
00:50:23.091 --> 00:50:24.313 line:82%
I am not a doctor.

476
00:50:24.397 --> 00:50:27.601 line:82%
-Oh! So you're a nurse
in this hospital, right?

477
00:50:28.202 --> 00:50:29.485 line:82%
I do not work here.

478
00:50:30.006 --> 00:50:32.035 line:82%
My father built this hospital

479
00:50:32.488 --> 00:50:34.771 line:82%
and he had left the decoration
of this room to me.

480
00:50:35.408 --> 00:50:39.120 line:82%
Since then I just come here
to spend some time with these kids.

481
00:50:39.620 --> 00:50:43.291 line:82%
-So, what do you do?
-Nothing.

482
00:50:43.374 --> 00:50:45.960 line:82%
Wow. I wish I could do nothing.

483
00:50:49.297 --> 00:50:52.842 line:82%
Excuse me? I have been wanting
to ask you something.

484
00:50:53.968 --> 00:50:58.473 line:82%
The other night I saw you at the station.
You were standing all alone.

485
00:50:58.890 --> 00:51:02.188 line:82%
The train came, and I turned to look
at you and you had walked away,

486
00:51:02.727 --> 00:51:06.647 line:82%
I couldn't understand anything,
were you waiting for someone?

487
00:51:08.941 --> 00:51:11.903 line:82%
If you do not want to talk about it
it's okay, no problem.

488
00:51:15.615 --> 00:51:18.596 line:82%
You saw the girl standing at the station,

489
00:51:19.827 --> 00:51:22.371 line:82%
but you did not see her red, bridal dress,

490
00:51:23.790 --> 00:51:29.003 line:82%
the henna on her hands,
the vermilion on her forehead,

491
00:51:30.346 --> 00:51:34.634 line:82%
It was Karva Chauth.
I was waiting for my husband.

492
00:51:45.102 --> 00:51:48.940 line:82%
No, no, son, if you can't pay today,
pay it tomorrow.

493
00:51:50.691 --> 00:51:51.859 line:82%
What are you doing, man?

494
00:51:53.152 --> 00:51:56.047 line:82%
-Hey, Sameer, come here.
-Yes?

495
00:51:56.371 --> 00:52:00.318 line:82%
Why are girls and boys giving red
and yellow flowers to one another today?

496
00:52:00.409 --> 00:52:01.806 line:82%
Kakeji, today is rose day.

497
00:52:01.887 --> 00:52:04.444 line:82%
-Rose day? You mean, the flower Rose day.
-Yes, sir.

498
00:52:05.081 --> 00:52:08.626 line:82%
I have heard about Republic day
Independence day, Happy Birthday.

499
00:52:08.709 --> 00:52:12.004 line:82%
-What is this Rose day all about?
-It is a very special day, sir.

500
00:52:12.088 --> 00:52:15.800 line:82%
Today, you can give any girl a rose
and tell her what you feel for her

501
00:52:15.883 --> 00:52:19.136 line:82%
-and she cannot refuse it.
-This is a very nice day.

502
00:52:19.220 --> 00:52:20.388 line:82%
Definitely, sir, see.

503
00:52:20.513 --> 00:52:22.962 line:82%
Yellow rose is for friendship,
and red rose is for love.

504
00:52:23.046 --> 00:52:25.638 line:82%
Hey, keep the yellow in your pocket,
I need only the red rose.

505
00:52:26.102 --> 00:52:28.159 line:82%
Why do you leave
all the cleaning up to me?

506
00:52:28.263 --> 00:52:29.627 line:82%
Navneet, these days you are...

507
00:52:36.320 --> 00:52:38.651 line:82%
Preetoji, where did you go?

508
00:52:42.326 --> 00:52:43.651 line:82%
Never mind Kakeji, never mind.

509
00:52:45.454 --> 00:52:47.568 line:82%
-Happy loose day, ma'am.
-What?

510
00:52:48.082 --> 00:52:50.751 line:82%
I mean, happy Rose day, ma'am.
Happy Rose day!

511
00:52:50.835 --> 00:52:51.836 line:82%
Rose day?

512
00:52:51.919 --> 00:52:53.588 line:82%
Yes, ma'am, today is a very special day.

513
00:52:53.671 --> 00:52:57.023 line:82%
Today you will have to accept Kake's
rose today you cannot refuse me.

514
00:52:57.717 --> 00:53:00.011 line:82%
-Is that so?
-Yes, ma'am, you can ask anyone.

515
00:53:00.094 --> 00:53:03.523 line:82%
No, Kakeji, why ask anyone?

516
00:53:04.348 --> 00:53:06.475 line:82%
Since you are saying today is Rose day,

517
00:53:07.101 --> 00:53:08.936 line:82%
why don't you put it with your own hands.

518
00:53:09.437 --> 00:53:11.279 line:82%
-What?
-Yes.

519
00:53:13.858 --> 00:53:15.843 line:82%
-Preetoji?
-Yes, sir.

520
00:53:15.927 --> 00:53:17.854 line:82%
You are really looking like Juliet.

521
00:53:18.863 --> 00:53:24.410 line:82%
Oh, my Romeo, on this occasion,

522
00:53:24.493 --> 00:53:26.794 line:82%
I want to give you something special.

523
00:53:27.788 --> 00:53:30.143 line:82%
-So give it, ma'am.
-Should I?

524
00:53:31.125 --> 00:53:32.540 line:82%
Then, here it is.

525
00:53:33.294 --> 00:53:35.046 line:82%
Eat sugar and die,

526
00:53:35.129 --> 00:53:38.471 line:82%
to hell with your Rose day,
do not mess with Preeto.

527
00:53:38.534 --> 00:53:40.968 line:82%
Happy Rose day. Happy Republic day.

528
00:53:41.510 --> 00:53:43.046 line:82%
One cheese burger for table three.

529
00:53:54.607 --> 00:53:58.986 line:82%
Forget friendship today, just say it.

530
00:54:08.871 --> 00:54:11.516 line:82%
-Hey, babe.
-Where the hell have you been, Deepak?

531
00:54:11.602 --> 00:54:14.961 line:82%
I have been waiting for you
for half an hour.

532
00:54:15.074 --> 00:54:16.128 line:82%
I'm sorry, babe.

533
00:54:16.212 --> 00:54:19.548 line:82%
What sorry, Deepak. You just do not care
for anyone else's time.

534
00:54:19.632 --> 00:54:23.174 line:82%
You see, I got late trying
to find you these beautiful flowers.

535
00:54:23.970 --> 00:54:25.008 line:82%
Happy Rose day, babe.

536
00:54:27.999 --> 00:54:30.267 line:82%
-Last time.
-Okay, my princess.

537
00:54:30.363 --> 00:54:32.316 line:82%
Now, give me a hug. Come on. Yeah!

538
00:54:37.248 --> 00:54:38.275 line:82%
That's my girl.

539
00:54:38.359 --> 00:54:41.438 line:82%
-Come on, let me introduce you to Sameer.
-Who's that?

540
00:54:45.908 --> 00:54:47.118 line:82%
-Sameer.
-Hi, Sanju.

541
00:54:47.368 --> 00:54:49.892 line:82%
This is my friend
whom I wanted you to meet.

542
00:54:50.871 --> 00:54:54.425 line:82%
-Shocked you, didn't I?
-Definitely, shocked me.

543
00:54:54.959 --> 00:54:59.338 line:82%
Deepak, this is Sameer,
my oldest and dearest friend.

544
00:54:59.922 --> 00:55:02.777 line:82%
And Sameer, this is Deepak,
the love of my life.

545
00:55:04.593 --> 00:55:07.939 line:82%
Nice to see you, man. Is this cafe yours?

546
00:55:08.389 --> 00:55:09.974 line:82%
No, I work here.

547
00:55:10.224 --> 00:55:13.452 line:82%
-You mean to say you're a waiter here.
-Yes.

548
00:55:14.805 --> 00:55:15.834 line:82%
Excuse me.

549
00:55:15.928 --> 00:55:18.482 line:82%
Okay, come on, come with us.
We have come to pick you up.

550
00:55:18.566 --> 00:55:20.164 line:82%
We're going for a movie with friends.

551
00:55:20.247 --> 00:55:22.319 line:82%
I can't come, Sanju. I have a lot of work.

552
00:55:22.403 --> 00:55:25.031 line:82%
Come on, Sameer,
you can take leave for one day.

553
00:55:25.356 --> 00:55:27.199 line:82%
No, I cannot. I have just joined here.

554
00:55:27.283 --> 00:55:29.702 line:82%
Okay, Sanjana. Let's go, we gotta go.
See you, dude.

555
00:55:30.202 --> 00:55:32.163 line:82%
-Come, no, Sameer.
-Really can't.

556
00:55:32.231 --> 00:55:33.686 line:82%
Come on, Sanjana.

557
00:55:34.790 --> 00:55:36.917 line:82%
Okay, see you.

558
00:55:37.001 --> 00:55:38.169 line:82%
And, Sanju...

559
00:55:40.212 --> 00:55:41.329 line:82%
Happy Rose day, Sanju.

560
00:55:45.612 --> 00:55:46.660 line:82%
Thanks.

561
00:55:59.065 --> 00:56:01.335 line:82%
So, what are you going to do now?

562
00:56:02.777 --> 00:56:03.863 line:82%
Nothing.

563
00:56:06.014 --> 00:56:07.490 line:82%
I'll just never meet her again.

564
00:56:09.849 --> 00:56:10.929 line:82%
Never go in front of her.

565
00:56:13.810 --> 00:56:14.829 line:82%
I'll just forget her.

566
00:56:15.664 --> 00:56:16.832 line:82%
Wonderful.

567
00:56:19.543 --> 00:56:22.622 line:82%
Very good. You're doing very well.

568
00:56:23.005 --> 00:56:24.381 line:82%
You're on the right track.

569
00:56:25.202 --> 00:56:28.583 line:82%
If I'm not mistaken, she's the same girl
for whom you crossed the gate that night.

570
00:56:28.666 --> 00:56:30.011 line:82%
-Right?
-Yes, sir.

571
00:56:30.387 --> 00:56:33.974 line:82%
And today you want to forget her,
just because she loves someone else.

572
00:56:34.767 --> 00:56:37.311 line:82%
Very good, that's really great.

573
00:56:38.270 --> 00:56:41.771 line:82%
Excuse me, sir, there are some people
who fall in love, but their love

574
00:56:42.525 --> 00:56:46.572 line:82%
is not reciprocated.
Everyone does not have your kind of luck.

575
00:56:49.115 --> 00:56:52.645 line:82%
I pray to God everyday, Karan,
that no one has my kind of luck,

576
00:56:54.245 --> 00:56:55.871 line:82%
especially not you three.

577
00:56:59.708 --> 00:57:01.394 line:82%
At least Sameer loves someone,

578
00:57:02.498 --> 00:57:07.299 line:82%
who he can see, whose laughter he can
hear, who he can speak to.

579
00:57:09.677 --> 00:57:11.053 line:82%
I can't even do that.

580
00:57:12.054 --> 00:57:13.139 line:82%
Why not, sir?

581
00:57:16.267 --> 00:57:21.063 line:82%
Because the girl I love... is no more.

582
00:57:24.066 --> 00:57:25.442 line:82%
She's dead.

583
00:57:28.779 --> 00:57:31.115 line:82%
-I'm sorry, sir.
-No, don't be.

584
00:57:32.074 --> 00:57:33.200 line:82%
I'm not.

585
00:57:33.742 --> 00:57:36.303 line:82%
I did not fall in love with her
on the condition

586
00:57:36.376 --> 00:57:37.955 line:82%
that she would live longer than me.

587
00:57:38.998 --> 00:57:43.127 line:82%
There are no conditions in love,
so there shouldn't be any regrets.

588
00:57:45.045 --> 00:57:50.509 line:82%
So what if today she is not with me,
I still love her the same way,

589
00:57:51.468 --> 00:57:53.678 line:82%
not because
I can't find someone else to love,

590
00:57:54.889 --> 00:57:59.518 line:82%
but because loving her makes me happy.

591
00:58:02.021 --> 00:58:07.151 line:82%
Whenever I miss her, I close my eyes
and she is with me.

592
00:58:09.658 --> 00:58:10.678 line:82%
Sameer...

593
00:58:11.780 --> 00:58:13.324 line:82%
You didn't fall in love with her

594
00:58:13.407 --> 00:58:16.744 line:82%
on the condition
that she will love you too,

595
00:58:18.078 --> 00:58:21.142 line:82%
but today, just because she loves
someone else, you wish to forget her.

596
00:58:23.792 --> 00:58:26.712 line:82%
Don't let your love be defeated so easily.

597
00:58:31.884 --> 00:58:33.666 line:82%
Love is just like life,

598
00:58:34.720 --> 00:58:37.483 line:82%
it's not always easy,
and it does not always bring happiness,

599
00:58:38.891 --> 00:58:44.855 line:82%
but when we do not abandon life,
why should we abandon love?

600
00:58:48.484 --> 00:58:51.528 line:82%
I'm sorry, that lecture dragged on a bit.

601
00:58:52.821 --> 00:58:55.282 line:82%
If Mr. Narayan Shankar sees you here,

602
00:58:55.616 --> 00:58:58.699 line:82%
then all the love stories will come
to an end today itself. Come on, go on.

603
00:58:59.063 --> 00:59:01.497 line:82%
-Thank you, good night. Go on, fast.
-Good night, sir.

604
00:59:04.792 --> 00:59:09.088 line:82%
Love is just like life,
it's not always easy

605
00:59:09.546 --> 00:59:11.280 line:82%
and it does not always bring happiness.

606
00:59:12.007 --> 00:59:16.025 line:82%
But when we do not abandon life,
why should we abandon love?

607
00:59:24.270 --> 00:59:26.522 line:82%
-Hi.
-Hi.

608
00:59:28.691 --> 00:59:30.206 line:82%
Made you wait for a long time?

609
00:59:34.818 --> 00:59:35.906 line:82%
I'm sorry.

610
00:59:36.789 --> 00:59:37.962 line:82%
It's okay.

611
00:59:39.578 --> 00:59:40.606 line:82%
Dance?

612
01:00:38.052 --> 01:00:43.717 line:82%
This is for hugging me that day.
I know what guys like you are all about.

613
01:00:44.266 --> 01:00:46.949 line:82%
But this time you have messed
with the wrong girl.

614
01:00:48.103 --> 01:00:50.541 line:82%
My name is Ishika Dhanrajgir,

615
01:00:50.754 --> 01:00:54.380 line:82%
and I can employ 100 boys
like you as servants in my house.

616
01:00:54.777 --> 01:00:58.447 line:82%
So next time, before fooling around

617
01:00:58.530 --> 01:01:02.590 line:82%
with any girl, remember this slap
and Ishika Dhanrajgir.

618
01:01:03.619 --> 01:01:05.589 line:82%
Come on, girls, let's go.

619
01:01:09.315 --> 01:01:10.773 line:82%
-You're okay.
-Excuse me?

620
01:01:27.267 --> 01:01:29.216 line:82%
Thank you, Miss Dhanrajgir.

621
01:01:30.521 --> 01:01:32.868 line:82%
By slapping me,
you have taught me a lesson.

622
01:01:34.608 --> 01:01:36.013 line:82%
Thank you very much.

623
01:01:37.152 --> 01:01:40.572 line:82%
But ma'am, this really was my first time,

624
01:01:41.573 --> 01:01:43.597 line:82%
and I was unaware
of the rules of this game.

625
01:01:44.535 --> 01:01:49.832 line:82%
I did not know one had to exchange one's
bank accounts before asking a girl out.

626
01:01:50.833 --> 01:01:51.834 line:82%
I didn't know.

627
01:01:52.418 --> 01:01:55.712 line:82%
If I knew this, I would have introduced
myself much earlier to you,

628
01:01:55.963 --> 01:01:57.381 line:82%
my name is Vikram Oberoi,

629
01:01:57.714 --> 01:02:00.488 line:82%
and my father is one of the leading
industrialists of this nation,

630
01:02:01.385 --> 01:02:06.765 line:82%
and if he wants, he can employ
your father, but I am so naive,

631
01:02:07.766 --> 01:02:10.329 line:82%
I was not aware of the importance
of all this.

632
01:02:11.603 --> 01:02:17.526 line:82%
I just knew
that I had seen a beautiful girl,

633
01:02:18.944 --> 01:02:22.781 line:82%
who I wanted to get to know,
and become friends with.

634
01:02:23.615 --> 01:02:29.329 line:82%
I thought this was enough to ask someone
out for a date. How stupid I was, right?

635
01:02:29.955 --> 01:02:34.793 line:82%
But now I have understood.
Next time I won't get slapped.

636
01:02:36.712 --> 01:02:39.381 line:82%
Thank you once again, Miss Dhanrajgir.

637
01:02:40.120 --> 01:02:41.229 line:82%
Thank you.

638
01:02:45.679 --> 01:02:47.220 line:82%
Come on, Ishika, come, let's go.

639
01:02:52.060 --> 01:02:54.870 line:82%
Hey, Vicky, well done, man.
You shut her up, man,

640
01:02:55.481 --> 01:02:59.985 line:82%
And I was not aware that my friend
was the son of such a rich man.

641
01:03:00.944 --> 01:03:03.906 line:82%
What do you think
if I was the son of such a rich man,

642
01:03:03.989 --> 01:03:06.700 line:82%
-would I be a waiter's friend?
-What? What do you mean?

643
01:03:06.783 --> 01:03:08.952 line:82%
-My dad works in a bank.
-What?

644
01:03:09.203 --> 01:03:12.414 line:82%
-Yes.
-Then, what was all this?

645
